definitions.definition: ( uncountable ) Solid residue from roasting coal in a coke oven ; used principally as a fuel and in the production of steel and formerly as a domestic fuel.
examples: The plant should produce approximately 550,000 tons of screened blast furnace coke per year.

main_definition: ( uncountable ) Solid residue from roasting coal in a coke oven ; used principally as a fuel and in the production of steel and formerly as a domestic fuel.

definitions.definition: Alternative letter-case form of Coke ( cola-based soft drink, especially Coca-Cola ) .
Alternative letter-case form of Coke ( a serving of cola-based soft drink, especially Coca-Cola ) .
Alternative letter-case form of Coke ( any soft drink, regardless of type ) .
